file=Engineering/nova/logical/book-requirements.md · h=name: book-requirements\ntype: logical (placeholder — awaiting operator-supplied source books per rule 0.6)\nassigned_agent: nova (Engineering / Mobile)\ndate_added: 2026-07-09\n · p:=The logical layer grounds nova's judgments in real, citable sources. nova is dormant by default; when active and until books arrive, its patterns are flagged **reasoning-based** (rule 0.6).\n · ca:sources (operator to supply; suggestions, not purchases nova made)=1. **A mobile-architecture text (framework-appropriate)** — grounds state management, navigation, and lifecycle patterns beyond the dated framework playbook.\n2. **The store review guidelines** (Apple + Google — dated, like platform playbooks) — the authoritative, frequently-changing rules for app-store-release-discipline; kept dated, not book-grounded.\n3. **A distributed-data / sync text** (shared with dana/raj) — grounds offline-sync conflict-resolution strategies (CRDTs, last-write-wins trade-offs) rather than convention.\n · cf:as reasoning-based (rule 0.6)=- Staged-rollout percentages (1/10/100 convention, not derived) and the crash-free thresholds to halt.\n- Conflict-resolution rule selection when the data's semantics are ambiguous.\n- Device-matrix breadth (which devices/OS versions are "representative") before real usage data.\n · ep:(when books arrive)=Patterns/thresholds extracted with citations into this folder; the skills updated to cite them; reasoning-based flags removed where a citation replaces them. Store guidelines stay dated (they change often). Coordinate the sync text with dana/raj (shared need).\n